description.narrative: Core principles of results-based management, planning and reporting were fully applied to programming. As part of the Strategic Moment of Reflection, UNICEF ECA refined its results framework: (i) underpinned by integrated approaches and value-for-money principles, (ii) prioritized to address key bottlenecks hindering the delivery of results for children, and (iii) aligned with the global, regional and national priorities, including the SDGs, Generation Unlimited and strengthening climate resilience. UNICEF improved results for children by developing a results-based rolling workplan and implementing strategic approaches to communication, advocacy and partnerships to advance the child rights advocacy agenda, including capacity to measure impact. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:17/01/2020
